HEADWORD: Underbuy
<hw>Un`der*buy"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To buy at less
than the real value or worth; to buy cheaper than.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>J. Fletcher.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

